   First Gov site Hispanic Yearbook: A Unique Resource and Referral Guide
   for Hispanic Americans 2001
   Resource and referral guide for Hispanic Americans provides useful
   information such as Federal and private sector employment
   opportunities, small business programs, and student scholarships and
   financial aid information. It also provides information about health,
   sports, education, media and Hispanic organizations, including contact
   information.
   In Their Own Words: Prenatal Care and Southeast Asian Women: Vietnamese
   Videotape
   This videotape encourages Southeast Asian women to seek prenatal care
   early in their pregnancies. Southeast asian women speak frankly of
   concerns about cultural differences in prenatal care and effective ways
   of incoprporating their traditional values into Western health care.
   A National Agenda for Nursing Workforce Racial/Ethnic Diversity
   Report discusses the need to have a culturally diverse workforce in
   order to meet our Nation's health care needs and issues related to
   racial/ethnic diversity in nursing education and practice. It presents
   goals and actions that can serve as national agenda to address those
   issues.
   The Allied Health Professions: Opportunities for Minority
   Students--Career Guidebook
   Guide presents information to encourage minority students to consider
   the allied health professions as career choices. Includes listings of
   programs that serve minorities, as well as information on scholarships
   and internships for minorities.

